  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Long-range correlations and bulk viscosity in the quark-gluon plasma</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-01</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">4</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We study long-distance features of the quark-gluon plasma, that are crucial for the dynamics of the system, with an infrared improved framework, the Gribov-Zwanziger quantization. Strikingly, at high temperature we uncover the presence of massless modes that violate the positivity of the quark spectral function. We also report on a study of transport coefficient, where we find a strong enhancement of the bulk viscosity that follows a scaling law similar to strongly coupled theories.</subfield>
